# Local dev tests for SharePointMcp — the 2-mode MCP server
#
# Requires: REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
#
# Transport: MCP Streamable HTTP at /mcp. Every call needs:
#   Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
# After `initialize`, follow-up calls MUST send the Mcp-Session-Id header
# returned by the initialize response. REST Client chains it automatically
# via named requests: {{mcpInit.response.headers.Mcp-Session-Id}}.
#
# Responses come back as SSE frames:  event: message \n data: { ...json... }
#
# ── 2 MODES ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Layer A (dev / bypass):  send NO Authorization header  -> server uses
#   DefaultAzureCredential (your `az login`); result.ResolvedVia == "app".
# Layer B (passthrough):   send  Authorization: Bearer {{token}}  -> server
#   acts AS THE USER (StaticTokenCredential); result.ResolvedVia == "user"
#   (SharePoint UPS is skipped in this mode — Graph /me still returned).
#
# Refresh a user token for Layer B (PowerShell) — paste over @token below:
#   az account get-access-token --resource https://graph.microsoft.com --query accessToken -o tsv | Set-Clipboard

@mcpUrl = http://localhost:8089

# Paste a Graph user token here for the Layer B passthrough tests
@token = PASTE_GRAPH_USER_TOKEN_HERE

###############################################################################
# Health probes
###############################################################################

### Liveness
GET {{mcpUrl}}/liveness

### Readiness
GET {{mcpUrl}}/readiness

###############################################################################
# LAYER A — developer identity (no Authorization header)
# Run these in order: initialize -> initialized -> list -> call
###############################################################################

# @name mcpInit
### A1. initialize (captures Mcp-Session-Id for the calls below)
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2024-11-05",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "1.0" }
  }
}

### A2. notifications/initialized (completes the handshake)
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcpInit.response.headers.Mcp-Session-Id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "notifications/initialized"
}

### A3. tools/list — expect get_sharepoint_profile
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcpInit.response.headers.Mcp-Session-Id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/list",
  "params": {}
}

### A4. tools/call get_sharepoint_profile — expect ResolvedVia: "app"
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcpInit.response.headers.Mcp-Session-Id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 3,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_sharepoint_profile",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

###############################################################################
# LAYER B — user passthrough (Authorization: Bearer {{token}})
# Uses its own session so it doesn't collide with Layer A above.
###############################################################################

# @name mcpInitUser
### B1. initialize (with user token)
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2024-11-05",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "1.0" }
  }
}

### B2. notifications/initialized
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcpInitUser.response.headers.Mcp-Session-Id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "notifications/initialized"
}

### B3. tools/call get_sharepoint_profile — expect ResolvedVia: "user"
POST {{mcpUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcpInitUser.response.headers.Mcp-Session-Id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 3,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_sharepoint_profile",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}
